The paper deals with natural language processing (NLP) and reasoning, which are core topics in the sub-category of Computation and Language (cs.CL). The paper also involves machine learning techniques for automatic problem solving, which falls under the sub-categories of Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) and Machine Learning (cs.LG). The paper also involves graph-based algorithms, which are relevant to the sub-category of Computing and Combinatorics (cs.CC). Finally, the paper involves the creation of a new annotated corpus, which is relevant to the sub-category of Sound and Music Computing (cs.SD), as annotated corpora are important for training and evaluating NLP models.
